{{Infobox UK legislation |short_title = Prevention of Social Housing Fraud Act 2013 |parliament = Parliament of the United Kingdom |long_title = |year = 2013 |introduced_by = [[Richard Harrington (politician)|Richard Harrington]]<ref name="introduced"> {{cite web |url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201213/cmhansrd/cm120620/debtext/120620-0001.htm#12062086000011 |title=House of Commons Hansard for 20 June 2012 |date=2012-06-20 |work=[[Hansard]] |publisher=[[Parliament of the United Kingdom]] |accessdate=2013-03-09}} </ref> |territorial_extent = England and Wales |royal_assent = 31 January 2013 |commencement = |repeal_date = |amendments = |repealing_legislation= |related_legislation = [[Housing Act 1988]] |status = Current |original_text = https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/bills/cbill/2012-2013/0016/cbill_2012-20130016_en_1.htm |legislation_history = http://services.parliament.uk/bills/2012-13/preventionofsocialhousingfraud/stages.html |revised_text = |use_new_UK-LEG = no |statute_book_chapter = 3 }}
'''The Prevention of Social Housing Fraud Act 2013''' (c. 3) is an Act of the [[Parliament of the United Kingdom]]<ref>[https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/bills/cbill/2012-2013/0016/13016.pdf] Parliament.uk</ref> which will create offences and make other provision relating to sub-letting and parting with possession of social housing and for connected purposes.
